Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses algorithms for achieving optimal caching schemes, which makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves optimization problems, which makes cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and concentration results, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category.
